What is the difference between an adaptive website and a fully responsive website?
Responsive website design means that the site is programmed to detect what type of device is being used and respon to it.
Adaptive website uses breakpoints and has designs setup for each breakpoint.


Describe what it means to be mobile first vs desktop first.
Mobile first is when you set up your html to a mobile breakpoint first.
desktop first is what we have been doing then catering to mobile.

What does font-size: 62.5% in the html tag do for us when using rem units?
because 62.5% of 16px (typical default browser font-size) is 10px. That would still make 1.6rem = 16px.

How would you describe preprocessing to someone new to CSS?
its a tool that lets you mange your css better by breaking it up into files.


What is your favorite concept in preprocessing? What is the concept that gives you the most trouble?
nesting and imports are my favorite concepts.
